modules.description: Parses email headers according to RFC5322, handling folded whitespace and extracting unstructured field values. Converts these values into structured representations such as email addresses or dates. Processes multiline fields commonly found in formats like Debian control files.

Parses raw byte sequences into a structured representation using a custom parsing combinator. It processes binary data and constructs instances of Unstrctrd.t based on defined format rules. This is used to decode network protocol messages and binary file headers.

The module provides parsing and manipulation of unstructured text following RFC5322, operating on custom types representing character sequences and handling folding whitespace (FWS) for text normalization. It supports use cases like processing email headers, HTTP 1.1 headers, and DEB formats, with functions to remove FWS, validate UTF-8, and canonicalize input.
